
Actor James Fox is Edwards brother.
Edward Fox's role as the cold-blooded assassin of THE DAY OF 
                  THE JACKAL is todate his best remembered role.
Edward Fox was born on April 13, 1937 in Chelsea, London, England.
In 2002 Edward Fox was awarded the O.B.E. (Officer of the order 
                  of the British Empire) Queen's New Year's Honours List for his 
                  services to acting. Fox is a graduate from RADA, and an Associate 
                  Member of RADA.
